<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-01-01T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-01-01T19:00:00-05:00" n="1266" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1266">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">867.24/12–2944: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-01-01T20:00:00-04:00">January 1,
                                    1945—8 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>7. Your 2427 of December 29 and your 2437 of December 30.<note n="19" xml:id="d1266fn19">
                                <ref target="frus1944v05#pg_912">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1944, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">v</hi>, pp. 912</ref> and <ref target="frus1944v05#pg_914">914</ref>, respectively.</note> You
                            are authorized to sign the proposed lend-lease agreement without the
                            accompanying proposed exchange of notes if necessary provided paragraph
                            4 of such notes is included in the agreement.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>